===Etymology===
After {{w|Alexandre Yersin}}, Swiss bacteriologist, + {{af|en|-ia}}.
===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|yersiniae}}
# A [[Gram-negative]] [[bacterium]], of the genus ''[[Yersinia]]'', that is an [[etiological]] agent of several [[disease]]s in animals and humans, notably ''[[Yersinia pestis]]'', which causes [[bubonic plague]].
